Saudi hikes Dec Light , Extra Light to Asia - traders . Saudi Arabia raised its price formula for December - lifting Arab Light and Extra Light crude oil to Asian customers by 15 to 30 cents per barrel while lowering Arab Heavy crude by 10 cents , traders said on Tuesday . The December term contract price for Arab Light was set at the Oman / Dubai differential plus 75 cents , compared with a premium of 60 cents for November , while the December price for Berri Extra Light was raised by 30 cents to a premium of $ 1 . 85 , traders said . The December contract price for Arab Heavy was set at the Oman / Dubai differential minus $ 1 . 15 , down 10 cents from its November discount . Arab Medium was priced at the Oman / Dubai differential minus 30 cents for December , unchanged from November , traders said . 
